adjectives.description: rockish (comparative more rockish, superlative most rockish)

entries.meaning: Like a rock; stony; (figuratively) hard; callous
examples: God did strike them with Egyptian and Babylonish rods, but there were no tears, no relentings, no returnings, but grew harder and harder, even to a rockish hardiness.

adjectives.description: rockish (comparative more rockish, superlative most rockish)

entries.meaning: (music) That has the characteristics of rock music.
